author: @sentdex
text: ***** Any time you find someone apparently just using magic numbers, the first stop should be documentation. Here, we're using np.linspace. Just google that, and you'll wind up here: http://docs.scipy.org/doc/numpy/reference/generated/numpy.linspace.html. From there, you can see the first 2 nums are "start" and "stop," then the 3rd parm is called "num." Via documents, num is the number of samples to generate, default would be 50.
